The model performance was evaluated using a rolling prediction framework. In each iteration, data from the preceding 18 months were used to train the model and predict the pollutant concentrations for the following day. This process was repeated continuously until predictions were generated and validated over a six-month evaluation period. The rolling approach enables the model to learn from continuously updated data, thereby reflecting operational forecasting conditions. The performance was assessed using several standard metrics R2, MAE, RMSE, and MAPE.\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
