				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${\mathrm{MJ}}/{\mathrm{m}}^{{\mathrm{2}}}$$\end{document}) showed a strong positive correlation with O3 concentration. This aligns with the mechanism by which intense solar radiation accelerates the photolysis of NO2, thereby promoting ozone formation33. Conversely, relative humidity was negatively correlated. This likely reflects the fact that high humidity induces stomatal opening in vegetation, enhancing the dry deposition of ozone through stomatal uptake, thereby inhibiting accumulation34.
